  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coalition for Anti-corruption Drive in Western Corridor of Northern Region.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Better and effective performance of School Feeding Programme improved by 80% in provision of regular ample and high quality  diets for 450 school pupils, particularly for 250 girl-children in 10 target schools in 2 districts.
2.  Access of 450 school pupils to 50% of learning &amp; teaching resources improved by 30% in use of capiatation grant by 10 headteachers in 10 target schools in 2 districts.
3.  Regularity and commitment of 40 school teachers increased by 80% in attendance and classroom hours demonstrated by 505 improvement performance of 450 school pupils.
4.  Commitment of 10 PTAs and 5 SMCs to improved school monitoring enhanced by 50% for better school pupil performance. 
5.  Support of 2 District GES Directorates and 2 District Assemblies improved by 30% in facilitating the reduction of corrupt practices in the 10 target schools.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Organise 24 Radio discussions and jingles and play-back (in English and three local languages) to sensitize the general public on corruption as it affects basic education and preventive measures.
2.  Conduct 20 project presentation and awareness raising on anti-corruption measures for schools and at community forums. 
3. Conduct 2 District stakeholder workshops for 40 participants each project district to discuss the project, relevant corruption issues, types of monitoring forms appropriate for effective monitoring of project at all levels. 
4. Conduct 2 district sensitization and training workshops for 40 SFP Caterers and Assistants on improved performance of school feeding programme. 
5.       Conduct 2 district sensitization sessions and 2 training workshops for selected 200 school pupils (100 girls and 100 boys) for data collection, monitoring of school feeding activities and procure all 7 monitoring forms and other logistics for the project.</narrative>
  </description>
